atque: this form, introduced by Halm, may account for ac ad of the best MSS. For the question whether the form ac is in itself possible before an initial c, cf. Hand, Tursell. 1 p. 4573 Reid on Ac. ii 11, 34, where the evidence is well dis— cussed. See also i 23, 54, note on the proposal to insert nc before consistat.

in Niptris: Pacuvius wrote a Latin play based upon Sophocles’ Νίπτρα ἢ Οδυσσεὺς ἁκανθοπλήξ. The plot turns upon the death of Ulysses shot with a bone of the sting-ray (τρυγόνος κέντρῳ) by his son Telegonus. XVelcker conjectured that Euryclea was introduced in the be- ginning of the play washing the feet of Ulysses‚ cf. Homer, Odyss. xix 349—468, and that the name Νίπτρα was due to this fact.
